FuncDef: The peer-public-key end command enables the system to return to the system view from the public key view. The peer-public-key end command enables the system to return to the system view from the public key view. By default, no peer-public-key is configured.
ParentView: DSA public key view,ECC public key view,Public key view,sm2 public key view
ExtraInfo: After a public key is configured, you can run the peer-public-key end command to return to the system view from the public key view.
